Proposed law further provides that the rules and regulations shall include but not be limited
to procedures and grounds for the removal of any consortium member.
Proposed law provides that each consortium member shall serve without compensation,
except members may receive reimbursement for expenses in accordance with the guidelines
of the entity they represent.
Proposed law requires the member from the Pennington Biomedical Research Center to
serve as the initial chairperson for two years.
Proposed law further requires the consortium, after the initial two year period, to elect a new
chairperson every two years.
Proposed law provides that the consortium shall elect a vice chairperson and may elect other
officers, if appropriate.
Proposed law provides that the domicile of the consortium shall be in East Baton Rouge
Parish; however, the consortium may hold meetings elsewhere in the state.
Proposed law requires the consortium to hold quarterly public meetings, unless otherwise
voted against by the members or by order or the chairperson.
Proposed law provides the procedure the consortium to host special meetings.
Proposed law requires each member participating on the consortium to assist as needed in
providing staff support.
Proposed law provides the functions of the consortium.
Proposed law requires the consortium to submit an annual written report that summarizes
the activities of the consortium. Proposed law provides the time period for when the report
shall be submitted and whom it shall be submitted to.
Proposed law defines "consortium", "Funding Priority Program for Women's Health
Initiatives", "Interagency Women's Health Agenda", "Perimenopause", "Menopause", and
"Postmenopause".
(Adds R.S. 40:1122)
